p> He continued: “She said, &#39;Wow, you&#39;re not going to pay me any more money, then I don&#39;t think I&#39;m going to do it&#39;. And they said, &#39;Well, you should feel yourself fortunate to be part of the <a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/marvel-cinematic-universe">Marvel Universe</a> .&#39; So she declined… We would&#39;ve made a bigger deal out of this, but it would have involved us watching the movies and we weren&#39;t going to do that”. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The 1982 Movie Draft |大局" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/WDxFoy7arAg?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> <em>Avengers: Endgame</em> went on to make almost $2.8billion at the worldwide box office, becoming one of the most successful films of all time and a landmark in the superhero genre. A variant of Proxima Midnight returned in the film, although she did not have any lines and wasn&#39;t played by Coon, although she did provide the voice of the character for TV show <em>What If…?</em></p><p> <em>The White Lotus</em> actor is not the first person to criticise Marvel for low-ball money offers. In 2021, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/marvel-criticised-over-claimed-5000-pay-artists-3015688">several comic book artists spoke out against the compensation payments many were receiving for films based on their work.</a></p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/the-white-lotus-star-carrie-coon-turned-down-marvel-over-low-pay-they-said-you-should-feel-fortunate-to-be-part-of-this-3851637">&#39;The White Lotus&#39; star Carrie Coon turned down Marvel over low pay: “They said, &#39;You should feel fortunate to be part of this&#39;”</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
 'Taskmaster' original stage show surfaces online featuring future fan-favourite contestants https://www.nme.com/news/tv/taskmaster-original-stage-show-surfaces-online-featuring-future-fan-favourite-contestants-3851628?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=taskmaster-original-stage-show-surfaces-online-featuring-future-fan-favourite-contestantsVictoria Luxford Thu, 03 Apr 2025 13:52:35 +0000 NewsTV News https://www.nme.com/?p=3851628 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="任务主管" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> The TV version celebrates its 10th anniversary this year</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/taskmaster-original-stage-show-surfaces-online-featuring-future-fan-favourite-contestants-3851628">&#39;Taskmaster&#39; original stage show surfaces online featuring future fan-favourite contestants</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="任务主管" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Taskmaster-hosts-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> Footage has emerged of the original stage incarnation of <a href="http://'Taskmaster' original stage show surfaces online featuring future fan-favourite contestants"><em>Taskmaster</em></a> , performed at The Edinburgh Fringe Festival in 2010.</p><ul><li> <strong>READ MORE:</strong> <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/tv-interviews/greg-davies-soundtrack-of-my-life-3433370">Soundtrack Of My Life: Greg Davies</a></li></ul><p> <em>Taskmaster</em> was created by <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/alex-horne">Alex Horne</a> , who plays the assistant to The Taskmaster, Greg Davies, on the series. It was originally a stage show with Horne playing the title role. The idea was inspired by <em>The Crystal Maze</em> , his work on <em>Big Brother</em> , and his envy of his close friend Tim Key winning the Edinburgh Comedy Award in 2009.</p><p> The original format saw him send 20 comedians monthly tasks by email over the course of a year. He then presented their efforts as part of a two-hour show at the 2010 Edinburgh Festival Fringe with the slightly different title <em>The Task Master</em> .</p><p> In the seven minute clip, Horne introduces the show, saying: “So this is The Task Master. This is the climax of a year&#39;s worth of work, it&#39;s 12 months of creativity for one performance, one strange evening tonight”. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Taskmaster Origins - Rare Footage of the First Ever Show! (Edinburgh 2010)" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/8Ei-z3iUp14?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> He then introduces the contestants: Dan Atkinson, Jarred Christmas, James Dowdeswell, Tim FitzHigham, Steve Hall, Tim Key, Lloyd Langford, Jodie Long, Henning Wehn, Joe Wilkinson, Mike Wozniak, Tom Wrigglesworth. Comedian Mark Watson was originally intended as a contestant but was absent due to illness.</p><p> Wilkinson (series two); Watson (series five); and Wozniak (series 11) would go on to appear on the TV incarnation. Langford appeared in series two of the Australian spinoff.</p><p> The footage then shows the tasks, which include: “Please deposit a sum of money into my Barclay&#39;s Bank account”; “Find a hedgehog”; and “Send me something large through the post. As with the televised version, posts are awarded on ingenuity and comedy value.</p><p> It is the origin of what would become a comedy TV institution, with the format being reworked in 2015 into the <em>Taskmaster</em> show that is currently standing at 18 series, including nine specials, 14 international spin-offs, a streaming service, and a <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/taskmaster-the-live-experience-to-launch-in-london-3760325">forthcoming live experience</a> .</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/tv/taskmaster-original-stage-show-surfaces-online-featuring-future-fan-favourite-contestants-3851628">&#39;Taskmaster&#39; original stage show surfaces online featuring future fan-favourite contestants</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
